  given task ≡ "Design invoice data model and database schema (fields, statuses, line items, tax handling)"
  yield steps[], estimated-hours

  ∴ Decompose «task» into 3-5 sequential steps. Each step should be:
    - A half-day to two-day work unit
    - Sequentially ordered (step N depends on step N-1)
    - Concrete enough to estimate hours

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield steps ≡ [
    "Research invoicing domain requirements (field standards, tax jurisdictions, line item patterns)",
    "Design entity-relationship model (Invoice, LineItem, Customer, Payment, TaxRate entities)",
    "Write database migration scripts (PostgreSQL DDL with constraints, indexes, triggers)",
    "Build seed data and validation tests (sample invoices, edge cases, referential integrity)"
  ]

  yield estimated-hours ≡ 28

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ 3 ≤ len(steps) ≤ 5 → ✓ (4 steps)
--   ⊨ steps are in dependency order → ✓ (research → design → implement → test)
--   ⊨ estimated-hours is a number → ✓ (28)

